  "14-13": (
    caption: [Conversion of galactose to glucose 1-phosphate. The conversion proceeds through a sugar-nucleotide derivative, UDP- galactose, which is formed when galactose 1-phosphate displaces glucose 1-phosphate from UDP-glucose. UDP-galactose is then converted by UDP-glucose 4-epimerase to UDP-glucose, in a reaction that involves oxi- dation of C-4 (light red) by NAD1, then reduction of C-4 by NADH; the result is inversion of the configuration at C-4. The UDP-glucose is recycled through another round of the same reaction. The net effect of this cycle is the conversion of galactose 1-phosphate to glucose 1-phosphate; there is no net production or consumption of UDP-galactose or UDP-glucose. c14GlycolysisGluconeogenesisandthePentosePhosphatePathway.indd Page 563 06/09/12 10:42 AM user-F408 c14GlycolysisGluconeogenesisandthePentosePhosphatePathway.indd Page 563 06/09/12 10:42 AM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop 14.3 Fates of Pyruvate under Anaerobic Conditions: Fermentation 563],
